{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place olive oil and leek into the mixing bowl, sauté <b>2 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add potato, porcini mushrooms, water, vegetable stock cube and cook <b>25 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>. Meanwhile, in a non-stick frying pan, lightly fry the ham until it is crispy and then transfer to a plate.","Check the potatoes and if necessary, prolong cooking time. Then blend <b>1 min\/speed 8<b>. Transfer soup into soup plates.","Garnish with the crispy ham, sprinkle with chives and add a dash of olive oil. Serve hot"]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["25 g extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for serving","80 g leek, finely sliced","380 g potatoes, peeled and cut into small pieces","10 g dried porcini mushrooms, soaked and squeezed","380 g water","1 tsp vegetable stock paste, homemade","1 slice smoked dry-cured ham (speck), cut into thin strips","4 stalks fresh chives, finely chopped"]}],"id":"r126913","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-7BSzo2q72ww\/XZMz10B1PsI\/AAAAAAAAa2A\/DHveYL0o8TIyzIDPeUjo1e9yNglCt1stACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_lO_EUP2nVz2YYQfY.png","title":"Leek and potato soup with crispy smoked ham","publishedAt":"2017-08-07T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.5 g","fat":"17.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"32.7 g","calories":"1347 kJ \/ 322 kcal"},"usefulItems":"plate, heat-proof soup bowls, non-stick frying pan, stove","hintsAndTricks":["Serve the soup with toasted bread.","The ham in this recipe is a lean, lightly smoked and dry cured ham from South Tyrol in northern Italy. It may be substituted with prosciutto."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","40m","2 portions"]}